cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SI. 

The paper discusses the sample complexity of multiclass prediction in several learning settings, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the design of good learners, which may fall into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) categories. Finally, the paper introduces new generalizations of Littlestone's dimension, which is a topic related to computational learning theory and may be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
